# Windowed-Spectator Leakage Budget Step-6 Next Test Is Sharpness Of The Repaired Sheet On The Friendly Stress Set

Status: `INFERRED` Step-6 next-test assignment from the repaired ledger

On the frozen canonical packet sheet, the first honest next theorem question
for `Windowed Spectator-Leakage Budget` is whether the repaired classwise
leakage sheet
`G_leak(P_n; I) = (L_tot, L_mirror, L_companion, L_feedback, L_cross)`
with budget vector
`(1/4, 1/12, 1/12, 1/16, 1/24)`
is the smallest friendly-admissible sheet supported by the carried stress set
`{F_SS(1/12), F_SL(1/16)}`
while hostile `F_DT(delta, eta)` remains excluded on the same frozen ledger
by the recorded total, mirror, companion, and feedback overloads.

This pair is the smallest meaningful carried-forward test object because no
single friendly packet saturates the repaired classwise sheet as sharply as
the pair does jointly.
So the next phase should treat the repaired sheet as a sharpness or minimality
theorem target on that exact stress set, not as a finished global obstruction
theorem.

Before any honest theorem or counterexample claim, the local record still
needs one exact classwise ratio ledger for the carried stress set,
one proof that each repaired coordinate is genuinely sharp there rather than
only numerically suggestive,
one explicit statement that hostile exclusion is driven by
`L_tot`,
`L_mirror`,
`L_companion`,
and
`L_feedback`
because the present record does not yet land one separate uniform hostile
cross-class gap above `1/24`,
and one same-currency transfer statement if the result is meant to upgrade
into a broader no-near-circuit obstruction claim.

The strongest claim currently supported is narrower:
the repaired object supports an exact classwise admissibility theorem on the
frozen packet ledger and gives the branch one concrete obstruction-facing
screen for later exact search.
It does not yet justify any theorem that passing
`G_leak`
forces template closeness, rules out all near-circuit behavior, or defines a
global near-circuit obstruction beyond the audited packet class and carried
calibration set.

